<div id="review_2628173601" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2628173601" />
    <a title="Elyse  Walters" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/597461-elyse-walters"><img alt="Elyse  Walters" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1514246949p2/597461.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2628173601?book_show_action=true">Sep 28, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elyse  Walters" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elyse  Walters" href="/user/show/597461-elyse-walters">Elyse  Walters</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2628173601" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12011256671231063584">Audiobook....narrated by Lee Ingleby and Emma Cunniffe<br/><br/>“Such as the ‘daisy’ came by symbolized childbirth, motherhood, and new beginnings”......<br/><br/>Personally I wouldn’t want to grow up with the name Daisy, (symbolizing innocence and purity), but I did wonder what happened to eight year old Daisy Mason on the night she was having a BBQ -costume party at her house in Oxford with friends and neighbors. <br/><br/>This is ‘book 1’ of a police procedural psychological thriller.....a British crime novel. The best co</span>
  <span id="freeText12011256671231063584" style="display:none">Audiobook....narrated by Lee Ingleby and Emma Cunniffe<br /><br />“Such as the ‘daisy’ came by symbolized childbirth, motherhood, and new beginnings”......<br /><br />Personally I wouldn’t want to grow up with the name Daisy, (symbolizing innocence and purity), but I did wonder what happened to eight year old Daisy Mason on the night she was having a BBQ -costume party at her house in Oxford with friends and neighbors. <br /><br />This is ‘book 1’ of a police procedural psychological thriller.....a British crime novel. The best compliment I could give the book is I’m interested in reading ‘book 2’. <br /><br />Detective Inspector, (DI Adam Farley), and his team wanted to know where Daisy was....as much as I did. Haha.....of course I want to know!<br />Following along, I questioned everyone: the parents, ( Barry and Sharon: who ‘seemed’ most obvious), the brother Leo, friends, extended family, neighbors, and others in the community. ....but I never guessed the final-FINAL ending. Not sure how plausible it was.....but......’maybe’?/! ...<br />Interesting anyway.....enough to have me intrigued about the next book. <br /><br />We follow the investigation, interviews, flashbacks, Twitter comments, and Facebook posts. People have numerous conspiracy theories, points of views, and accusations....that give social media folks a thrill in which to dig their teeth into. <br />My teeth were in digging too. “Close To Home”, worked really well in audiobook format. I was constantly drawing conclusions and making assumptions about Sharon, Barry, and Leo. I even question DI Fawley, and his entire team. Fawley carried distress like a heavy sack of potatoes— <br />The Mason family ( peeling layers of an onion here), show their colors: pretty-on-the-outside-while-perfectly-troubled &amp; dysfunctional-just-below-the-surface. <br /><br />A quick-zip-a-Dee-Doo-Dah to the end......dead or alive? Foul play or a runaway? <br />Suspenseful with twists and turns.... or? .....flat as a pancake?<br /><br />For me....it was enjoyable....(not a flat pancake at all.....but also not WOW-Z either). <br /><br />Like a daisy.....cheerful, wild, and disheveled......Cara Hunter sprinkles this psychological thriller with decorative different sizes and colors. <br />She loves me....<br />She loves me not....<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="12011256671231063584" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


