<div id="review_3832654692" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3832654692" />
    <a title="Kat (Books are Comfort Food)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/25532045-kat-books-are-comfort-food"><img alt="Kat (Books are Comfort Food)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1617935580p2/25532045.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3832654692?book_show_action=true">Feb 12, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kat (Books are Comfort Food)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kat (Books are Comfort Food)" href="/user/show/25532045-kat-books-are-comfort-food">Kat (Books are Comfort Food)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/37768390-close-to-home">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3832654692" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17175951310608649094">I thoroughly enjoyed this book. Started off well and kept me going. <br/><br/>I’d probably rename it, Nasty Parents. The parents, Barry and Sharon Mason, are a piece of work. Barry is never home and Sharon cares only about keeping up appearances. By the end of the book I loathed them both! <br/><br/>The day of a costume party, little Daisy, goes missing, from her own home. I don’t want to say too much here because there is a twist and I want you to enjoy it! Daisy is 8 years old, quite precocious, a little wicked a</span>
  <span id="freeText17175951310608649094" style="display:none">I thoroughly enjoyed this book. Started off well and kept me going. <br /><br />I’d probably rename it, Nasty Parents. The parents, Barry and Sharon Mason, are a piece of work. Barry is never home and Sharon cares only about keeping up appearances. By the end of the book I loathed them both! <br /><br />The day of a costume party, little Daisy, goes missing, from her own home. I don’t want to say too much here because there is a twist and I want you to enjoy it! Daisy is 8 years old, quite precocious, a little wicked and also sweet. <br /><br />The book is full of well-timed twists and turns. Some of the twists you might see coming but most won’t. You’ll do plenty of guessing as to whom really is responsible and your guesses will change based on new information that floats to the surface. <br /><br />It’s interesting that In the story they post online comments from neighbors and readers regarding the case. The comments range from sympathy to snarky. Most are jagged swords aimed at the parents stupidity. It makes me wonder how much social media platforms can affect shape and outcome, especially when cases go to court. <br /><br />I enjoyed some of the characters, while I disliked others. I liked DI Adam Falley, the main investigator. <br /><br />The book begins the evening of the crime and then alternates before the crime and the current timeline. <br /><br />Bottom line: Loved the book, good character development and good character take-downs, clever, well paced and some goon one-liners. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17175951310608649094" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


